{"nodes":[{"content":"Call Base Class Constructor","pos":[2,29]},{"pos":[31,106],"content":"To call a base class constructor from a subclass, use the keyword <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>base<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>:","source":"To call a base class constructor from a subclass, use the keyword **base**:"},{"content":"If a base class has a default (no parameter) constructor, you can omit an explicit constructor call:","pos":[268,368]}],"content":"# Call Base Class Constructor\n\nTo call a base class constructor from a subclass, use the keyword **base**:\n\n```PowerShell\nclass A \n{\n    [int]$a\n\n    A([int]$a)\n    {\n        $this.a = $a\n    }\n}\n\nclass B : A\n{\n    B() : base(103) {}\n}\n\n[B]::new().a # return 103\n```\n\nIf a base class has a default (no parameter) constructor, you can omit an explicit constructor call:\n\n```PowerShell\nclass C : B\n{\n    C([int]$c) {}\n}\n```"}